SECTION 2: DEFINITIONS & KEY CONCEPTS
================================================================================

OBJECT-ORIENTED PROGRAMMING (OOP)

OOP is a programming paradigm that organizes code into objects containing both
data (attributes) and methods (functions) that operate on that data.

Key OOP Concepts Used:

1. CLASS
   Definition: A blueprint or template for creating objects
   Example: Patient class defines structure for patient objects
   Usage: public class Patient { ... }

2. OBJECT
   Definition: An instance of a class with specific values
   Example: Patient p = new Patient("John", "pass123", "9876543210", 35, "O+");

3. ENCAPSULATION
   Definition: Wrapping data and methods together, hiding internal details
   Example: Private fields (username, password) accessed via public methods

4. PACKAGES
   Definition: A namespace that organizes related classes
   Example: 
   - pack1: Contains Patient class
   - pack2: Contains HospitalAdmin, Doctor, Medicine, Room classes
   - pack3: Contains MainApp class

5. CONSTRUCTOR
   Definition: Special method that initializes objects when created
   Example: public Patient(String username, String password, ...) { ... }

6. METHODS
   Definition: Functions that define behavior of objects
   Example: register(), login(), bookAppointment()

ARRAYS

Definition: A collection of elements of the same type stored in contiguous
memory locations.

Usage in Project:
- Patient[] patients = new Patient[100]  // Stores up to 100 patients
- Doctor[] doctors = new Doctor[20]      // Stores up to 20 doctors
- Medicine[] pharmacy = new Medicine[20] // Stores up to 20 medicines
- Room[] rooms = new Room[20]            // Stores up to 20 rooms

VALIDATION

Definition: Process of checking if input data meets specified criteria before
processing.

Examples in Project:
- Mobile validation: Must be 10 digits, starting with 9/8/7/6
- Password validation: Minimum 6 characters
- Blood group validation: Only valid types (A+, A-, B+, B-, O+, O-, AB+, AB-)
- Age validation: Must be between 1 and 119

AUTHENTICATION

Definition: Process of verifying user identity before granting access.

Implementation:
- Registration: Creates new user account with validated data
- Login: Verifies username, password, and mobile number
- Three login attempts allowed for security

