9.4 COMMON MISTAKES TO AVOID

1. Array Index Out of Bounds
   ✗ Accessing array[count] instead of array[count-1]
   ✓ Always check i < array.length or i < count

2. Null Pointer Exception
   ✗ Accessing methods on null objects
   ✓ Check if object != null before use

3. String Comparison
   ✗ Using == for string comparison
   ✓ Use .equals() method

4. Scanner Issues
   ✗ Not consuming newline after nextInt()
   ✓ Use scanner.nextLine() after nextInt()

5. Array Full Check
   ✗ Not checking if array is full
   ✓ Check count < array.length before adding

6. Case Sensitivity
   ✗ Not handling case in comparisons
   ✓ Use .equalsIgnoreCase() for usernames

